article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- — Vonterius Woolbright had 22 points, 16 rebounds and five assists in Western Carolina's 69-65 win against Tennessee Tech on Tuesday night. Russell Jones added 14 points for the Catamounts (6-0). DJ Campbell finished with 12 points. Jayvis Harvey led the way for the Golden Eagles (2-5) with 17 points. Daniel Egbuniwe added 13 points, 10 rebounds and four assists for Tennessee Tech. David Early had 15 points and Josiah Davis finished with 14. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
